rel=me

The  me  keyword for the  rel  attribute of the  <link>  and  <a>  elements indicates that the current
resource is represented by the linked party. The  me  value was introduced in the XHTML Friends Network
(XFN) specification .

html

```html
<link rel="me" href="example.com" />
```

The  rel="me"  attribute is used in RelMeAuth and Web sign in specifications as a way to enable a person
to identify themselves to a web service using their domain name or a particular URL.

