<big>: The Bigger Text element

Deprecated: This feature is no longer recommended. Though some browsers might still support it, it may
have already been removed from the relevant web standards, may be in the process of being dropped, or may
only be kept for compatibility purposes. Avoid using it, and update existing code if possible; see the
<L=P#f>compatibility table</L> at the bottom of this page to guide your decision. Be aware that this
feature may cease to work at any time.

The  <big>  HTML deprecated element renders the enclosed text at a font size one level larger than the
surrounding text (  medium  becomes  large  , for example). The size is capped at the browser's maximum
permitted font size.

Warning: This element has been removed from the specification and shouldn't be used anymore. Use the CSS
 font-size  property to adjust the font size.

<L=P#4>Attributes</L><I=4>
This element has no other attributes than the global attributes , common to all elements.

<L=P#5>Examples</L><I=5>
Here we see examples showing the use of  <big>  followed by an example showing how to accomplish the same
results using modern CSS syntax instead.

<L=P#6>Using big</L><I=6>
This example uses the obsolete  <big>  element to increase the size of some text.

HTML

html

```html
<p>
  This is the first sentence.
  <big>This whole sentence is in bigger letters.</big>
</p>
```

Result

<L=P#9>Using CSS  font-size </L><I=9>
This example uses the CSS  font-size  property to increase the font size by one level.

CSS

css

```html
.bigger {
  font-size: larger;
}
```

HTML

html

```html
<p>
  This is the first sentence.
  <span class="bigger">This whole sentence is in bigger letters.</span>
</p>
```

Result

<L=P#d>DOM interface</L><I=d>
This element implements the  HTMLElement  interface.

<L=P#e>Specifications</L><I=e>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  HTML
  # big

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=P#f>Browser compatibility</L><I=f>
BCD tables only load in the browser <!-- -->with JavaScript enabled. Enable JavaScript to view data.

<L=P#g>See also</L><I=g>
- CSS:  font-size  ,  font 
- HTML:  <small>  ,  <font>  ,  <style> 
- HTML 4.01 Specification: Font Styles
