<figcaption>: The Figure Caption element

Baseline Widely available

This feature is well established and works across many devices and browser versions. It’s been available
across browsers since July 2015 .

- Learn more
- <L=1g#9>See full compatibility</L>
- Report feedback

The  <figcaption>  HTML element represents a caption or legend describing the rest of the contents of its
parent  <figure>  element, providing the  <figure>  an accessible description .

<L=1g#4>Try it</L><I=4>
<L=1g#5>Attributes</L><I=5>
This element only includes the global attributes .

<L=1g#6>Examples</L><I=6>
Please see the  <figure>  page for examples on  <figcaption>  .

