The  <rt>  HTML element specifies the ruby text component of a ruby annotation, which is used to provide
pronunciation, translation, or transliteration information for East Asian typography. The  <rt>  element
must always be contained within a  <ruby>  element.

<L=2q#4>Try it</L><I=4>
See the article about the  <ruby>  element for more examples.

<L=2q#5>Attributes</L><I=5>
This element only includes the global attributes .

<L=2q#6>Examples</L><I=6>
<L=2q#7>Using ruby annotations</L><I=7>
This example provides Romaji transliteration for the kanji characters within the  <ruby>  element:

html

```html
<ruby> 漢 <rt>Kan</rt> 字 <rt>ji</rt> </ruby>
```

```html
body {
  font-size: 22px;
}
```

Result

