The  style  global attribute contains CSS styling declarations to be applied to the element. Note that it
is recommended for styles to be defined in a separate file or files. This attribute and the  <style> 
element have mainly the purpose of allowing for quick styling, for example for testing purposes.

<L=3y#4>Try it</L><I=4>
Note: This attribute must not be used to convey semantic information. Even if all styling is removed, a
page should remain semantically correct. Typically it shouldn't be used to hide irrelevant information;
this should be done using the  hidden  attribute.

